Narran is believed to be derived from a local Aboriginal word.

Narran County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is bounded by the Culgoa River on the west, the Narran River in the east, the Queensland border in the north, and the Barwon River in the south. It includes Goodooga and the area to the north of Brewarrina .
